{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/testexpectmessage(logdomain:loglevel:pattern:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"testExpectMessage"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"logDomain"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">? = nil, "},{"text":"logLevel","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"LogLevelFlags","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/LogLevelFlags","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib13LogLevelFlagsV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"pattern","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!)","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When this message is logged, it will not be printed, and the test case will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not abort.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This API may only be used with the old logging API ([func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.log"},{"type":"text","text":"] without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_LOG_USE_STRUCTURED"},{"text":" defined). It will not work with the structured logging","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"API. See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"logging.html#testing-for-messages","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use [func"},{"code":"GLib.test_assert_expected_messages","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] to assert that all","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"previously-expected messages have been seen and suppressed.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can call this multiple times in a row, if multiple messages are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"expected as a result of a single call. (The messages must appear in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same order as the calls to [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.test_expect_message"},{"text":"].)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For example:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["\/\/ `g_main_context_push_thread_default()` should fail if the","\/\/ context is already owned by another thread.","g_test_expect_message (G_LOG_DOMAIN,","                       G_LOG_LEVEL_CRITICAL,","                       \"assertion*acquired_context*failed\");","g_main_context_push_thread_default (bad_context);","g_test_assert_expected_messages ();"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that you cannot use this to test [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.error"},{"type":"text","text":"] messages, since"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.error","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] intentionally never returns even if the program doesn’t"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"abort; use [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.test_trap_subprocess","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] in this case.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If messages at [flags","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.LogLevelFlags.LEVEL_DEBUG"},{"text":"] are emitted, but not explicitly","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"expected via [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.test_expect_message"},{"text":"] then they will be ignored.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/testExpectMessage(logDomain:logLevel:pattern:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"testExpectMessage(logDomain:logLevel:pattern:)","externalID":"s:4GLib17testExpectMessage9logDomain0E5Level7patternySPys4Int8VGSg_AA03LogG5FlagsVAItF","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Function","symbolKind":"func","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"testExpectMessage","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"logDomain","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar"},{"text":">?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"logLevel","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib13LogLevelFlagsV","text":"LogLevelFlags"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"pattern"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">!)"}]},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Indicates that a message with the given ","type":"text"},{"code":"logDomain","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"logLevel"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with text matching "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pattern"},{"type":"text","text":", is expected to be logged."}],"refere